  "text": "The principal chooses the parameters for each of the schemes to maximize his expected profits: E i,j (y i − wage i ) subject to standard incentive compatibility and individual rationality constraints. He takes as given the parameters of the environment, which are the coefficient of absolute risk aversion of agents r, the distributions of the two shocks i and η, the structure of the cost function of effort and the outside option of the agents which we denote byv. The agents choose their effort levels simultaneously after learning The framework described above can be extended to more than 2 agents. [CITATION_1] The extension of the IPR and the T scheme is rather straightforward, while if the RPR scheme is employed then agent i gets",
